    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A method for dating fired clay objects, which is based on accurate measurement of the hydroxyl content of fired clays, as well as accurate determination of the chemical kinetics of rehydroxylation or chemical recombination of fired-clay ceramics with environmental moisture.</Note_Text>
